00074 /*  Tip: To avoid modifying this file each time you need to switch between these
00075         devices, you can define the device in your toolchain compiler preprocessor.
00076 
00077  - Ultra Low Power Medium-density devices are STM32L151xx and STM32L152xx 
00078    microcontrollers where the Flash memory density ranges between 64 and 128 Kbytes.
00079  - Ultra Low Power Medium-density Plus devices are STM32L151xx, STM32L152xx and 
00080    STM32L162xx microcontrollers where the Flash memory density is 256 Kbytes.
00081  - Ultra Low Power High-density devices are STM32L151xx, STM32L152xx and STM32L162xx 
00082    microcontrollers where the Flash memory density is 384 Kbytes.
00083   */

00284 #if defined ( __CC_ARM   )
00285 /* ARM Compiler
00286    ------------
00287    RAM functions are defined using the toolchain options. 
00288    Functions that are executed in RAM should reside in a separate source 
00289    module. Using the 'Options for File' dialog you can simply change the 
00290    'Code / Const' area of a module to a memory space in physical RAM.
00291    Available memory areas are declared in the 'Target' tab of the 
00292    'Options for Target' dialog. 
00293 */
00294  #define __RAM_FUNC FLASH_Status 
00295 
00296 #elif defined ( __ICCARM__ )
00297 /* ICCARM Compiler
00298    ---------------
00299    RAM functions are defined using a specific toolchain keyword "__ramfunc". 
00300 */

00302 
00303 #elif defined   (  __GNUC__  )
00304 /* GNU Compiler
00305    ------------
00306    RAM functions are defined using a specific toolchain attribute 
00307    "__attribute__((section(".data")))". 
00308 */
00309  #define __RAM_FUNC FLASH_Status __attribute__((section(".data")))
00310

00316 */
00317  #define __RAM_FUNC  FLASH_Status

00319 #endif

06320 
06321 #define CLEAR_BIT(REG, BIT)   ((REG) &= ~(BIT))
06322

06324

06326

06328 
06329 #define READ_REG(REG)         ((REG))
06330
